// Cognitive Reasoning Contracts v1
//
// Domain message types for the deterministic cognitive augmentation layer.
// These define the shared vocabulary between cognitive COGs — the data shapes
// that flow through the reasoning pipeline.
//
// Separation of concerns:
//   gears-contracts  → infrastructure (manifests, governance, Forge)
//   cog-contracts    → domain (this file, plus Envelope, ConfigPatch, etc.)
//
// These types are designed to support both PURE and HYBRID cognitive COGs.
// PURE COGs operate on the structured fields directly. HYBRID COGs receive
// their input from the Claim Extractor (I-1), which is the single point of
// LLM dependency in the pipeline.

